code:
line 262:
if (line_already_counted == 0)
                        {
                                lines_of_code++;
                                line_already_counted = 1;
                        }


line 160:
 if ( lines_of_code < 0 )        //STONESOUP:CROSSOVER_POINT
                {
                   while ( 0 == 0 )     //STONESOUP:TRIGGER_POINT       // TECHNICAL_IMPACT:DOS
                   { lines_of_code++; }
                }


reason:
In line 262, no overflow is checked, and once the variable lines_of_code is overflow, it will be a negative number, then in line 160, it will go into the infinite while loop

solution: change line 270
if (line_already_counted == 0)
                        {
				if(lines_of_code<127)
                                {lines_of_code++;}
				else 
				{printf("exceed the maximum line"); exit(1);}
                                line_already_counted = 1;
                        }


OR
if (line_already_counted == 0)
                        {
				
                                lines_of_code++;
				if(lines_of_code<0)
				{printf("exceed the maximum line"); exit(1);}
                                line_already_counted = 1;
                        }


